++ ## Prerequisites
++ 
++-- [just](https://github.com/casey/just) - command runner
++-- [Bun](https://bun.sh) - JS runtime (auto-evolve-cli)
++-- [uv](https://docs.astral.sh/uv/) - Python package manager (autoresearch-modal)
++-- [Modal](https://modal.com) account - GPU training (`modal setup` for one-time auth)
+++- [Git](https://git-scm.com) — project must be a git repo with at least one commit
+++- [just](https://github.com/casey/just) — command runner
+++- [Bun](https://bun.sh) — JS runtime (auto-evolve-cli)
+++- [uv](https://docs.astral.sh/uv/) — Python package manager (autoresearch-modal)
+++- [Modal](https://modal.com) account — GPU training (`modal setup` for one-time auth)
++ 
++ ## Quick Start
++ 
++ ```bash
++-# Install everything
++-just install
++-
++-# --- auto-evolve-cli ---
++-just cli-build              # compile
++-just cli-link               # build + register global `auto-evolve` command
++-just cli-check              # lint + format + typecheck + test
++-just cli-dev -- init        # run in dev mode without building
++-
++-# --- autoresearch-modal ---
++-modal setup                 # one-time Modal auth
++-just modal-deploy           # deploy Modal app
++-just modal-train            # run training on H100 (~5 min, ~$0.33)
++-just modal-prepare          # download data + train tokenizer
+++just install          # install all dependencies (cli + modal)
+++just cli-link         # build CLI + register global `auto-evolve` command
+++modal setup           # one-time Modal auth
+++just modal-deploy     # deploy Modal app to your account
++ ```
++ 
++-See [auto-evolve-cli/README.md](./auto-evolve-cli/README.md) and [autoresearch-modal/README.md](./autoresearch-modal/README.md) for full docs.
++-
++ ## How It Works
++ 
++-1. **Initialize** - `auto-evolve init` creates config, `program.md` template, and a git branch
++-2. **Define** - edit `program.md` with objective, metric, eval command, and scope
++-3. **Baseline** - `auto-evolve baseline` runs eval once to record starting metric
++-4. **Loop** - `auto-evolve loop` autonomously hypothesizes, implements, evaluates, and keeps or reverts
+++Auto-evolve turns any measurable codebase into an autonomous experiment loop. You define what to optimize and how to measure it; the AI agent does the rest.
+++
+++### 1. Initialize
+++
+++```bash
+++cd autoresearch-modal          # or any git repo
+++auto-evolve init
+++```
+++
+++Creates `.auto-evolve/` config dir, a `program.md` template, an `experiments/` folder, and a new git branch.
+++
+++### 2. Define your program
+++
+++Edit `program.md` to specify the objective, metric, eval command, files in scope, and constraints. This is the only file the human maintains — it tells the agent what to optimize and how to measure success.
+++
+++```markdown
+++## Objective
+++Minimize val_bpb for a fixed 5-minute training run.
+++
+++## Metric
+++- **Name**: val_bpb
+++- **Direction**: lower_is_better
+++- **Extract command**: grep "^val_bpb:" run.log | tail -1 | awk '{print $2}'
+++
+++## Eval Command
+++`uv run modal_runner.py`
++ 
++-The `autoresearch-modal` package is a ready-made target: it uses auto-evolve to autonomously optimize a GPT training script on Modal H100s.
+++## Scope
+++- You may modify `train.py` to optimize for val_bpb.
+++```
++ 
++-## All Commands
+++See [auto-evolve-cli/README.md](./auto-evolve-cli/README.md) for the full `program.md` reference.
++ 
++-Run `just` at the root to see all available recipes:
+++### 3. Establish a baseline
++ 
+++```bash
+++auto-evolve baseline
++ ```
++-install             # Install all dependencies
++-check               # Run all checks (lint + format + typecheck + test)
++-
++-cli-install         # Install CLI dependencies
++-cli-build           # Build CLI
++-cli-link            # Install CLI globally (build + bun link)
++-cli-test            # Run CLI tests
++-cli-test-watch      # Run CLI tests in watch mode
++-cli-lint            # Lint CLI
++-cli-lint-fix        # Lint CLI with auto-fix
++-cli-format          # Format CLI code
++-cli-format-check    # Check CLI formatting
++-cli-typecheck       # Type-check CLI
++-cli-check           # Run full CLI quality check
++-cli-dev             # Run CLI in dev mode (pass args after --)
++-
++-modal-install       # Install Modal project dependencies
++-modal-deploy        # Deploy Modal app
++-modal-train         # Run training on Modal H100
++-modal-format        # Format Modal project code
++-modal-format-check  # Check Modal project formatting
++-modal-prepare       # Prepare data (download + tokenizer)
+++
+++Runs the eval command once on unmodified code and records the starting metric. This is the number the loop will try to beat.
+++
+++### 4. Run the loop
+++
+++```bash
+++auto-evolve loop --max-experiments 20
++ ```
+++
+++Each iteration:
+++
+++1. **Hypothesize** — agent generates ranked hypotheses (skipped if pending ones remain)
+++2. **Implement** — agent picks the top pending hypothesis and edits files in scope
+++3. **Evaluate** — runs eval command, extracts metric
+++4. **Keep or revert** — if the metric improved, keep the commit; otherwise `git revert`
+++5. **Log** — appends to `history.jsonl`, `results.tsv`, and archives artifacts to `experiments/<id>/`
+++
+++The loop stops at `--max-experiments`, `--max-failures` consecutive failures, or Ctrl+C.
+++
+++### 5. Review results
+++
+++```bash
+++auto-evolve status              # dashboard: baseline, best, improvement, stats
+++auto-evolve report              # generate a markdown report of all experiments
+++```
+++
+++## Example: autoresearch-modal
+++
+++The `autoresearch-modal` package is a ready-made target. It uses auto-evolve to autonomously optimize a GPT training script running on Modal H100s (~$0.33/run, ~5 min each).
+++
+++```bash
+++cd autoresearch-modal
+++auto-evolve init
+++auto-evolve baseline
+++auto-evolve loop --max-experiments 20    # ~2 hours, ~$6.60
+++auto-evolve status
+++```
+++
+++Or use the shortcut from the repo root:
+++
+++```bash
+++just evolve                     # run the loop from autoresearch-modal/
+++```
+++
+++## Commands
+++
+++### auto-evolve CLI
+++
+++| Command | Description |
+++|---------|-------------|
+++| `auto-evolve init` | Create `.auto-evolve/`, `program.md` template, config, git branch |
+++| `auto-evolve baseline` | Run eval once and record the starting metric |
+++| `auto-evolve loop` | Run the autonomous experiment loop |
+++| `auto-evolve status` | Print dashboard: baseline, best, improvement, hypothesis stats |
+++| `auto-evolve report` | Generate a human-readable markdown report |
+++| `auto-evolve config view` | Print current config as JSON |
+++| `auto-evolve config get <key>` | Print a single config value |
+++| `auto-evolve config set <key> <value>` | Update a config value |
+++
+++### just recipes
